						<summary>

						<p>Stone standing in the inner, <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of Mahaliṅgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Āḷuvarasa, circa 7th century.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record seems to refers to the reign of Āḷuvarasa and his feudatory Kundavarmmarasa and states that Guṇḍaṇṇa was in charge of the <hi rend="italic">nāṭṭu-mudime</hi> (administration of the <hi rend="italic">nāḍu</hi>) and Ādakappa Viddeṟeya was holding the <hi rend="italic">vara</hi> probably of some land in a subdivision <hi rend="italic">(banna ?)</hi> which was being governed by Sattigāri. It refers to a gift of money (? <hi rend="italic">Kañchu</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Kīḻgañchu</hi>) on the orders of Chiriyaṇṇas. Kanakaśiva wrote the record.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
